\begin{proof}
  \uses{def:push_pull_obj, lem:isIso_modules_of_toPresheaf, lem:pushPull_binary_coprod_prod}
  Argue by induction on the finite index type \(\iota\), iterating the binary decomposition.

  \emph{Empty base.} If \(\iota\) is empty, \(\coprod_i \mathrm{legs}\,i\) is the initial scheme;
  pulling \(\mathcal{F}\) back and pushing forward along the (unique) initial structure map yields the
  terminal object of \(X.\mathrm{Modules}\), which is the empty product \(\prod_{i \in \emptyset}
  \operatorname{pushPullObj}\mathcal{F}\,(\mathrm{legs}\,i)\). The comparison map is an isomorphism on
  the underlying presheaf of abelian groups (both sides have zero sections over every open), so by
  Lemma~\ref{lem:isIso_modules_of_toPresheaf} it is an isomorphism in \(X.\mathrm{Modules}\).

  \emph{Inductive step.} Split off one index, writing \(\iota \simeq \{*\} \sqcup \iota'\) with
  \(\iota'\) of strictly smaller cardinality. The coproduct \(\coprod_{i \in \iota} \mathrm{legs}\,i\)
  reassociates as the binary coproduct of \(\mathrm{legs}\,*\) and \(\coprod_{i \in \iota'}
  \mathrm{legs}\,i\), and the structure map \(\operatorname{Sigma.desc}(i \mapsto
  (\mathrm{legs}\,i).\mathrm{hom})\) becomes the \(\operatorname{coprod.desc}\) of \((\mathrm{legs}
  \,*).\mathrm{hom}\) and the tail structure map \(\operatorname{Sigma.desc}(i \in \iota' \mapsto
  (\mathrm{legs}\,i).\mathrm{hom})\). By Lemma~\ref{lem:pushPull_binary_coprod_prod} the push--pull
  object on this binary coproduct is the binary product of \(\operatorname{pushPullObj}\mathcal{F}\,
  (\mathrm{legs}\,*)\) and the push--pull object on the tail coproduct
  \(\operatorname{Over.mk}(\operatorname{Sigma.desc}(i \in \iota' \mapsto (\mathrm{legs}\,i).\mathrm{hom}))\);
  the induction hypothesis identifies the latter with \(\prod_{i \in \iota'}
  \operatorname{pushPullObj}\mathcal{F}\,(\mathrm{legs}\,i)\). Composing the binary product with the
  indexed product over \(\iota'\) gives the indexed product over \(\iota\), as claimed. (All
  isomorphisms produced live in \(X.\mathrm{Modules}\); where the reassociation of the coproduct is
  needed it is verified through the underlying presheaf by
  Lemma~\ref{lem:isIso_modules_of_toPresheaf}.)
\end{proof}

